{
  "stem": "14928.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But then it doesn't take long to get, you know, accent, but I never really had a Jewish accent in school, so I didn't have any trouble.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But other children did, because there were teachers, anti-Semites, and they used to make fun of them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They used to say, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So they, they didn't feel good.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Now, when you get older, you start reading and knowing more.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We, we felt it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But I can't say that it was in, in our little town.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "When I came to Lodz already, when I was 15, there were all kind of non-Jewish organizations, like Nazi organizations, and they used to march in the streets.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they used to have all kinds of [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] announcements.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In 1935 already, they used to have announcements not to buy Jews in Lodz, all over.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were Haller's Army, they called them, which they were Nazis.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They wore gray uniforms, and they used to march in the streets with all kind of, you know, announcements or something saying about Jews.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I didn't like the small town, and I used to all the time ask my older sisters, how could they stay in such a small town?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There are no movies, no theaters, no nothing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I guess they didn't mind it, so-- but when I got to, you know, that age and I just figured, there's nothing to do for me there.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If you learn something to do, you just can't-- you can't use it, for money for, you know, for learning.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was not in style girls should work in small towns-- not girls.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the, the father had to support all the family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I was-- I don't know why.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's was my-- that's the way my thinking was.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
